    <procedureSteps>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>1</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Examine the Brakes</stepTitle>
            <para>Examine the condition of the brakes.</para>
            <para>Open the brake quick release.</para>
            <para>Examine the condition and thickness of the brake pads.</para>
            <para>Make sure there is a large quantity of rubber left.</para>
            <para>Make sure the pad is not too hard.</para>
            <para>Clean all unwanted material.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>2</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Inspect Brake Installation</stepTitle>
            <para>Do an inspection of the installation of the brakes.</para>
            <para>Check the hydraulic brake system function.</para>
            <para>Refer to Hydraulic brake function for more information.</para>
            <para>Make sure there is sufficient clearance between the pad and the inner diameter of the brake surface.</para>
            <para>Caution: If the position of the pads is too low on the rim, the pads can move, causing separation of the spokes from their mountings.</para>
            <para>Refer to Brake pad seating for more information.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>3</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Check Tire Pressure</stepTitle>
            <para>Do a check of the tire pressure using the Tire pressure gauge.</para>
            <para>Compare the value read with the recommended pressure shown on the sidewall of the tire.</para>
            <para>Add necessary air.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>4</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Examine Wheels</stepTitle>
            <para>Examine the condition of the wheels.</para>
            <para>Examine the rims for bulges and dents.</para>
            <para>Examine for splits at the seam where an extruded rim is bonded.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>5</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Check Headset Bearings</stepTitle>
            <para>Straddle the bicycle.</para>
            <para>Apply the front brakes and push the handlebars forward.</para>
            <para>Make sure the headset bearings are tight.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <stepNumber>6</stepNumber>
            <stepTitle>Check Chain</stepTitle>
            <para>Visually examine the chain.</para>
            <para>If the chain is too dirty, clean it as specified in the Clean chain task.</para>
            <para>Visually examine the chain for links that are frozen or do not move easily.</para>
            <para>Apply necessary lubricant.</para>
            <para>Do a check of the chain to make sure it is tight.</para>
            <para>Make sure the play of the chain is not too much.</para>
        </step>
    </procedureSteps>
